** New Incentive Mechanism**
- It's going to make things a LOT more competitive/ difficult to earn incentive if you don't take it seriously. Better crack open those textbooks and study up.

 - The scoring will be much more complex. We're going to track more metrics for every miner, like profit,loss, sharpe ratio over multiple time frames, and more. - Ultimately, the top scored miners will need to have provable, long term performance over thousands of predictions
- This doesn't mean it will be impossible for new miners to get there, but you're going to have to prove your worth to climb the ranks

- If you're here predicting for your favorite team, or following picks of some guy on twitter hoping to make a quick buck, this is no longer going to be a way to stay registered, sorry to say.

**How can I stay competitive?**
- Research. Learn to develop a strict strategy, implement risk boundaries for yourself, think like a pro. There are some decent resources out there, but ultimately, the best will be clever, have a very thorough understanding of probability/stats, and use all tools available to them to make the best decisions. We will release more models soon, which we hope to continuously improve. Models can help you ingest and analyze a lot more data.
